transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you so much for calling Bazzardite.

Speaker 2: My name is Jessie.

Speaker 1: May I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Eugene Banks.

Speaker 1: Okay, just a moment.

Speaker 2: Great, and Mr. Banks, how can I help you?

Speaker 1: I was calling today about your refund.

Speaker 2: What it is, I'm going on my third bottle

Speaker 1: and I can't tell no difference or anything.

Speaker 2: I'm gonna have to go on my third bottle.

Speaker 1: Gotcha, oh, I'm so sorry to hear that.

Speaker 2: Okay, let me look up your account, okay?

Speaker 1: Hold on one second.

Speaker 2: Mr. Banks, what's your zip code?

Speaker 1: 41465.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Are you at 250 Old Burning Fork Road,

Speaker 2: Saylorsville, Kentucky?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Oh, I'm sorry to hear it's not a fit for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me go ahead and do this.

Speaker 2: Are you at Banks Clan 1968 at Gmail?

Speaker 1: Yes, yes.

Speaker 2: We'll send you an email with return instructions.

Speaker 1: Just return whatever you have left over

Speaker 2: and a refund will be issued to the card

Speaker 1: that was used to order, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, so there'll be a return label on the email?

Speaker 1: No, you'll have to do it yourself.

Speaker 2: And we don't cover the return, but...

Speaker 1: And then you have to make sure that it's postmarked

Speaker 2: no later than the 24th, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, I'll do that then.

Speaker 2: Great, thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Thank you, bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
